# (''biochemistry'') relating to [[structural biology]], which describes the general [[three-dimensional]] form of local regions of [[biopolymers]], such as [[protein]]s and [[DNA]]. It does not, however, refer to specific positions in three-dimensional space, which are considered to be tertiary structure. The secondary structure of a protein may include regions of [[alpha helix]], [[3_10 helix]], [[pi helix]], [[beta sheet]], [[beta turn]], [[omega loop]], and [[random coil]].